{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Produce a surf report\n",
    "\n",
    "The `SurfReport` object features additional reporting functionalities, such as plotting methods and easily readable surf reports."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from pysurfline import SurfReport"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "List of known spot id\n",
    "\n",
    "| Spot Id | Name |\n",
    "|---|---|\n",
    "| 5842041f4e65fad6a7708890 | Pipeline (USA)|\n",
    "| 584204204e65fad6a7709b09 | Varazze (ITA)|\n",
    "| 5842041f4e65fad6a7708b4b | Uluwatu (IDN)\n",
    "| 5842041f4e65fad6a7708c8e | La Graviere (FRA)|"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Initializing a `SurfReport` objects does nothing else than calling a `SpotForecast` object with the specified `params` for requesting the desired response data by the Surfline API. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "['ForecastGetter(Type:wave, Status:200)',\n",
       " 'ForecastGetter(Type:wind, Status:200)',\n",
       " 'ForecastGetter(Type:tides, Status:200)',\n",
       " 'ForecastGetter(Type:weather, Status:200)']"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 2,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "params = {\n",
    "    \"spotId\": \"5842041f4e65fad6a7708890\",\n",
    "    \"days\": 3,\n",
    "    \"intervalHours\": 3,\n",
    "}\n",
    "report = SurfReport(params)\n",
    "report.api_log\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "With respect to the `SpotForecast` objects, that stores separately all the raw response data as class attributes, the `SurfReport` object has the additional `df` attribute to easily inspect all the hourly data fetched from the Surfline servers merged into a readable `pandas.DataFrame` object."

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",

   "source": [
    "Lets then call the `plot()` method, that returns a `matplotlib` figure representing the minimum and maximum **surf size** that is forecasted for the spot.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Daylight hours** are shown in the plot, with darkgrey representing night and lightgrey representing dusk and dawn.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Wind speed and direction** is annotated at the top."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1800x1200 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "f=report.plot()\n",
    "f.savefig(\"../images/surfreport_pipeline.jpeg\")"
   ]
